@therevtank2100 @machonachomedia Not really. This only affects the PSX, which is a superset of the PS2 for DVR. 

Sony at this point was aware of PS2 HDD exploits, and used PSX as a means of testing better security. 

In the end, it didn't matter and Sony focused their efforts on PS3 ROM hardware security.
